15 Section 1 further requires the Administrator to adopt regulations: (1) concerning
16 the implementation of such a communication system; and (2) that prescribe
17 standards for training that certain employers are required to provide to certain
18 employees. Additionally, section 1 prohibits the regulations adopted by the
19 Administrator from imposing additional liability on an employer for the purposes of
20 certain policies of insurance. Finally, section 1 provides that these requirements do
21 not apply to any employer that: (1) is an operator of a mine; (2) employs
22 commercial truck drivers; (3) is a provider of emergency services; or (4) has 10 or
23 fewer employees.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 618 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Administrator shall establish by regulation:
4 (a) Measures that an employer must take to monitor air quality
5 and reduce the exposure of an employee to poor air quality from
6 wildfire smoke where:
7 (1) The air quality index is 150 or more but less than 200;
8 and
9 (2) The air quality index is 200 or more; and
10 (b) An air quality index level caused by wildfire smoke at
11 which an employer shall not allow an employee to perform critical
12 tasks outdoors.
13 2. Each employer shall establish a communications system in
14 accordance with the requirements adopted by regulation pursuant
15 to subsection 3 that:
16 (a) Informs an employee, in a manner that is understandable
17 to the employee, when the employee is being exposed to air quality
18 where the air quality index is 150 or more during the employee’s
19 shift and of the protective controls that are available to the
20 employee to reduce exposure to the air quality.
21 (b) Allows any employee to inform the employer when the
22 employee is being exposed to air quality where the air quality
23 index is 150 or more in the employee’s workplace and if the
24 employee is experiencing any symptom related to such exposure,
25 including, without limitation, asthmatic attacks, difficulty
26 breathing or chest pain.
27 3. The Administrator shall adopt regulations that prescribe:
28 (a) Requirements for the implementation of a communications
29 system established pursuant to subsection 2. Such regulations may
30 prescribe additional requirements for such a communications
31 system.
