– 3 –
1 (b) Standards for an employer to train employees who work
2 outdoors and may be exposed to poor air quality from wildfire
3 smoke. Such standards must require that the training:
4 (1) Be provided in a manner that is understandable to the
5 employee;
6 (2) Describe the requirements imposed on employers
7 pursuant to this section; and
8 (3) Describe the risks of not using personal protection
9 equipment while working outdoors and being exposed to poor air
10 quality from wildfire smoke.
11 4. The Administrator may develop and provide to each
12 employer written guidance for complying with this section and any
13 regulations adopted pursuant thereto. Such guidance may account
14 for working conditions in rural and remote locations.
15 5. The regulations adopted pursuant to this section must not
16 impose any additional liability on an employer for the purposes of
17 industrial insurance or insurance for occupational diseases.
18 6. The provisions of this section do not apply to any employer
19 who:
20 (a) Is an operator of a mine;
21 (b) Employs commercial truck drivers;
22 (c) Is a provider of emergency services; or
23 (d) Has 10 or fewer employees.
24 7. As used in this section:
25 (a) “Outdoors” means a work environment where an employee
26 regularly performs job duties in conditions that are directly
27 affected by the elements. The term does not include a work
28 environment that is enclosed or climate controlled.
29 (b) “Provider of emergency services” means an agency of the
30 State or a political subdivision of the State that provides police,
31 fire-fighting, rescue, emergency medical services or other services
32 related to public safety. The term includes, without limitation, any
33 entity that provides such services during a state of emergency or
34 declaration of disaster proclaimed pursuant to NRS 414.070.
35 (c) “Wildfire smoke” means smoke caused by a wildfire which
36 contains a complex mixture of gases and particles that includes,
37 without limitation, gases, hazardous air pollutants, water vapor
38 and particle pollution.
39 Sec. 2. The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any
40 additional expenses of a local government that are related to the
41 provisions of this act.
42 Sec. 3. 1. This section and section 2 of this act become
43 effective upon passage and approval.
44 2. Section 1 of this act becomes effective:
